Initial conformational searches were carried out using Spartan 10 software with the Merck Molecular Force Field (MMFF) (
). The conformers with a Boltzmann population of over 1% were chosen for ECD calculations. The conformers were subjected to gas-phase QM geometry optimizations and frequency calculations at B3LYP/6-31 + G before solvated geometry optimizations at M062X/TZVP with SDM-IEFPCM in MeOH. The ECD spectra for all conformers of compounds 1 , 3 , 4 , 9 , and 16 were conducted by time-dependent density functional theory (TD-DFT) methodology at the ω B97X/def2-TZVP using IEFPCM in methanol, CAM-B3LYP/TZVP with IEFPCM in MeOH, and M062X/def2-TZVP with IEFPCM in MeOH (
). The ECD spectra were generated using the program SpecDis v1.71 from dipole-length rotational strength by applying Gaussian band shapes with sigma = 0.2 eV (
).
